to refresh your palate [inaudible].

00:16:37.690 --> 00:16:42.580 position:56%
I don't know if [inaudible]
comparisons [inaudible] of any sort,

00:16:42.580 --> 00:16:47.710
but they arise by virtue
of the processes

00:16:47.710 --> 00:16:49.080
which I'm applying [inaudible].

00:16:49.080 --> 00:16:53.130
It may be in some sections
there are more notes there

00:16:53.130 --> 00:16:55.220
because I cut fewer notes out.

00:16:55.220 --> 00:16:59.690
One long note may be there
because I cut out all the notes

00:16:59.690 --> 00:17:04.980
which would have been around
it by following a sort of,

00:17:04.980 --> 00:17:07.970
some sort of intellectual
[inaudible].

00:17:07.970 --> 00:17:13.220 position:56%
And a lot of things that I do in my
music start out as a tremendous sort

00:17:13.220 --> 00:17:18.330
of bustle of materials like the
rhythmic structures of this work,

00:17:18.330 --> 00:17:23.730
22 layers and they go on for
140 pages [inaudible] 140 pages.

00:17:23.730 --> 00:17:29.060
[laughter] Then I find
secondary procedures to them,

00:17:29.060 --> 00:17:30.800
which either brings
out particularity

00:17:30.800 --> 00:17:34.040
of the rhythmic process at that
moment on that level or seeks

00:17:34.040 --> 00:17:36.740
to obscure it by eliminating it
compared with something else.

00:17:36.740 --> 00:17:40.410
So really that's what's happening
is [inaudible] you've got a sort

00:17:40.410 --> 00:17:45.950
of mental rubber as you're rubbing
out things, and you are meant

00:17:45.950 --> 00:17:50.430
to feel time differently, because
when time is filling itself

00:17:50.430 --> 00:17:54.170
